<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="-NAqvfsSd6EsS_R3q9uM0-A" name="assign_weights,_ulEb4JjUEd6JmoH2XFiafA" guid="-NAqvfsSd6EsS_R3q9uM0-A" changeDate="2009-10-26T11:11:06.046-0700" version="7.5.0">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Not all assessment criteria are equal. Some are more important than others. Assessment criteria are weighted according&#xD;
    to their relative importance to the overall solution. The weighting factors are normalized to add up to 1.0. This task&#xD;
    should be performed in collaboration with stakeholders and relevant domain experts.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <sections xmi:id="__pwSoMJaEd6Ame-XMnb0Gg" name="Assign relative weights to the assessment criteria" guid="__pwSoMJaEd6Ame-XMnb0Gg">
    <sectionDescription>Assign a weight to each assessment criterion based upon&amp;nbsp;its relative importance such that the sum of all weights&#xD;
equals 1.0.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_EhonkMJbEd6Ame-XMnb0Gg" name="Update the Trade Study Report" guid="_EhonkMJbEd6Ame-XMnb0Gg">
    <sectionDescription>Capture the assessment criteria weights in the Trade Study Report.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>In order to prioritize the assessment criteria and to allow direct comparison between them, each criterion is assigned a&#xD;
weighting factor.</purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
